20/04/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso expressed hope for further positive developments in Greek-Turkish relations during a visit to Athens on Tuesday (19 April). Speaking to top government officials, Barroso praised Greece's support for Turkey's EU membership bid. He also reiterated that the sealing of an enlarged customs protocol, including Cyprus, is the main prerequisite for starting accession talks with Ankara in October. 
Also Tuesday, the Greek Parliament ratified the new EU Constitution, becoming the sixth EU member to green light the document. It was endorsed by a vote of 268-17, with 15 abstentions. (ANA, MPA, TurkishPress.com, AP, AFP, BBC - 19/04/05)
